comment: /**  * Push a new prompt to be used by the shell.  * @param prompt the prompt  * @see #popPrompt()  */
code: /**  * Push a new prompt to be used by the shell.  * @param prompt the prompt  * @see #popPrompt()  */ public void pushPrompt(String prompt) {     this.prompts.push(prompt). }

comment: /**  * Pop a previously pushed prompt, returning to the previous value.  * @see #pushPrompt(String)  */
code: /**  * Pop a previously pushed prompt, returning to the previous value.  * @see #pushPrompt(String)  */ public void popPrompt() {     if (!this.prompts.isEmpty()) {         this.prompts.pop().     } }

comment: /**  * Returns the current prompt.  * @return the current prompt  */
code: /**  * Returns the current prompt.  * @return the current prompt  */ public String getPrompt() {     return this.prompts.isEmpty() ? DEFAULT_PROMPT : this.prompts.peek(). }
